{
  "_comment": [
    "=============================================================",
    "classifications.json — THE ONLY FILE THAT EVER CHANGES",
    "=============================================================",
    "WHAT THIS FILE DOES:",
    "  This is the single source of truth for every bucket, prefix,",
    "  and retention rule in the entire OCI lifecycle system.",
    "  Both Terraform (infrastructure) and the Python upload router",
    "  (application) read directly from this file.",
    "  There is no other place where routing or retention rules live.",
    "",
    "READ BY:",
    "  - terraform/main.tf          at deploy time (jsondecode + file())",
    "  - router/oci_upload_router.py at runtime    (json.load)",
    "",
    "OWNED BY:   Cloud ops / Data governance team",
    "CHANGED BY: Cloud ops admin only",
    "",
    "HOW TO ADD A NEW CLASSIFICATION:",
    "  1. Add one JSON block below following the existing pattern",
    "  2. Run: terraform apply",
    "  3. Done — Python router picks it up automatically on next start",
    "     No code changes. No developer needed.",
    "",
    "FIELD REFERENCE:",
    "  bucket        : OCI bucket name the object routes to",
    "  prefix        : Folder path within the bucket  (must end with /)",
    "  archive_days  : Days after upload to move to Archive tier",
    "                  null = skip archive, go straight to delete",
    "  delete_days   : Days after upload to permanently delete",
    "=============================================================",
    "NOTE: JSON does not support comments natively.",
    "This _comment array is intentionally ignored by all consumers."
  ],

